    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1675"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1675">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/689.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Diaz</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">President</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Informed by the United States Minister, Doctor Jefferson, of the best personal
                    efforts of yourself and Mr. Bryan to relieve our distressing condition, I beg
                    Your Excellency kindly to accept my cordial thanks together with the expression
                    of my firm confidence in the success of your good and deeply appreciated
                    endeavors in behalf of Nicaragua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adolfo Díaz</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
